<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-009-346 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 503 594</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 19 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM RTP unit receives North Carolina quality award.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Achievements and awards).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Achievements and AwardsState GovernmentNorth Carolina.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM RTP Unit Receives North Carolina Quality Award 11/19/91 TRIANGLE PARK,NORTH CAROLINA, U.S.A., 1991 NOV 19 (NB) -- IBM has announced that NorthCarolina governor James G. Martin will present the IBM RTP personal systemsmanufacturing team with the first annual North Carolina quality leadershipaward at a banquet on November 19th.andM;The North Carolina quality leadership award is the state's equivalent of theMalcolm Baldrige national quality award and is based on the same criteria.andO;There are categories for large and small manufacturing and for servicebusinesses that are judged to excel.andP;  IBM is the first recipient of the awardand is the only company to receive this award in 1991.andM;The 26 year-old IBM manufacturing facility at RTP has produced a wide varietyof personal computer and communications equipment.andP;  The manufacturingoperations employ approximately 2,100 people and occupy 1.2 millionsquare-feet.andP;  Products currently manufactured in the plant include PersonalSystems (PS/1 andamp; PS/2) computer units, PS monitors, display monitors anddisplay logic units.andM;A press forum will be held on November 20 beginning at 9:30 a.m.andP;  in room220, second floor of the North Carolina state university's McKimmon center inRaleigh.andP;  Forum panelists will include: Richard L. Daugherty, vice-president,manufacturing, IBM entry systems division; Braxton Vick, executivevice-president, Carolina Freight Carriers Corporation; and Wayne D. Peterson,president, Carolina Telephone.andM;Daugherty told Newsbytes: &quot;I am proud to accept the award on behalf of allthe people who worked so hard to achieve this honor.andP;  While receiving thishonor is a step in the right direction for us, it is not our ultimate goal.andO;As our customers increase their expectations and raise the bar, our qualityefforts must continually evolve to meet those changing demands.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19911119/Press Contacts: JulieAtkinson, RTP Press Forum, 919-733-4856; R.Pierce Reid, IBM, 919-543-5729)</TEXT></DOC>